    "created_at": "2012-11-24T02:20:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-11-24T02:20:55Z",
    "body": "I would definitely keep `get_ref()` and lose `with()`.  In general, I think that the `with()` pattern is better written using lifetimes and immutable pointers.  In this case, we have to rely on some unsafe code to get it to type check, but the interface is safe.\n",
